Given the clinical presentation of primary microcephaly, intellectual disability, and a sloping forehead from birth in the proband, the following differential diagnoses can be considered:

1. Microcephalic Osteodysplastic Primordial Dwarfism Type II
2. Seckel Syndrome
3. MOPD Type I (Microcephalic Osteodysplastic Primordial Dwarfism Type I)
4. Autosomal Recessive Primary Microcephaly
5. Cornelia de Lange Syndrome
6. Meier-Gorlin Syndrome (Ear-Patella-Short Stature Syndrome)
7. Cri-du-Chat Syndrome

These diagnoses are ranked according to the likelihood and the typical presentation of symptoms outlined in the case.
